{"id":719655,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ron_Fairly","text":"Ronald Ray Fairly (July 12, 1938 \u2013 October 30, 2019) was an American Major League Baseball player and broadcaster. He was born in Macon, Georgia. He played for the Los Angeles Dodgers, Montreal Expos, St. Louis Cardinals, Oakland Athletics, Toronto Blue Jays and the California Angels. He broadcasted for the Seattle Mariners.\nFairly died on October 30, 2019 of cancer in Indian Wells, California at the age of 81.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Major_League_Baseball","surface_form":"Major League Baseball","offset":69},{"uri":"Sports_commentator","surface_form":"broadcaster","offset":102},{"uri":"Macon%2C_Georgia","surface_form":"Macon, Georgia","offset":130},{"uri":"Los_Angeles_Dodgers","surface_form":"Los Angeles Dodgers","offset":164},{"uri":"Montreal_Expos","surface_form":"Montreal Expos","offset":185},{"uri":"St._Louis_Cardinals","surface_form":"St. Louis Cardinals","offset":201},{"uri":"Oakland_Athletics","surface_form":"Oakland Athletics","offset":222},{"uri":"Toronto_Blue_Jays","surface_form":"Toronto Blue Jays","offset":241},{"uri":"California_Angels","surface_form":"California Angels","offset":267},{"uri":"Seattle_Mariners","surface_form":"Seattle Mariners","offset":309},{"uri":"Cancer","surface_form":"cancer","offset":362},{"uri":"Indian_Wells%2C_California","surface_form":"Indian Wells, California","offset":372}]}